{{Nihongo|'''Tsuyoshi Watanabe'''|渡辺 剛|Watanabe Tsuyoshi|born 5 February 1997}} is a Japanese [[Association football|football]] player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[Feyenoord]]<ref>{{J.League player}}</ref> and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==Club career==
Watanabe joined [[J1 League]] club [[FC Tokyo]] in 2018.{{citation needed|date=January 2025}} On 4 January 2021, he started for FC Tokyo in the [[2020 J.League Cup final|final]] of the J.League Cup against [[Kashiwa Reysol]]. FC Tokyo won 2–1 to claim the third [[J.League Cup]] in club history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Japan – List of League Cup Winners |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tablesj/japleagcuphist.html |website=[[RSSSF]] |access-date=17 May 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=【公式】柏vsFC東京の試合結果・データ（ＪリーグYBCルヴァンカップ：2021年1月4日）：Ｊリーグ.jp |url=https://www.jleague.jp/match/leaguecup/2021/010401/live/#recap |website=Ｊリーグ.jp（日本プロサッカーリーグ） |access-date=24 August 2022 |language=ja}}</ref>

On 28 December 2021, Watanabe signed a three and a half year contract with [[K.V. Kortrijk|Kortrijk]] in Belgium.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=[[K.V. Kortrijk|Kortrijk]]|url=https://www.kvk.be/nieuws/eerste-japanner-bij-kv-kortrijk/|title=EERSTE JAPANNER BIJ KV KORTRIJK|date=28 December 2021|access-date=9 February 2022|language=nl}}</ref> On 1 July 2023, Watanabe moved to fellow [[Belgian Pro League|Pro League]] club [[KAA Gent]] on a permanent deal for a fee of €3,500,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/09-06-2023/kaa-gent-verwelkomt-tsuyoshi-watanabe|title=KAA Gent verwelkomt Tsuyoshi Watanabe &#124; KAA Gent Website|website=KAA Gent}}</ref>

On 23 July 2025, Watanabe joined [[Eredivisie|Dutch]] side [[Feyenoord]] on a four year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/officieel-feyenoord-lost-met-watanabe-eerste-defensieve-probleem-op |title=Officieel: Feyenoord lost met Watanabe eerste defensieve probleem op |trans-title=Official: Feyenoord fixes first defensive issues with Watanabe |language=Dutch |date=23 July 2025 |access-date=23 July 2025}}</ref> On 12 August, he scored his first two goals for the club in a 5–2 defeat to [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League qualifying|third qualifying round]] of the UEFA Champions League.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2045722--fenerbahce-vs-feyenoord/|title=Fenerbahçe SK 5-2 Feyenoord|website=UEFA|date=12 August 2025|access-date=11 November 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 1 January 2024, Watanabe  was selected by manager [[Hajime Moriyasu]] as a member of the Japan squad at the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://jfa.jp/eng/news/00033539/ |title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) squad - AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023 |date=1 January 2024 |publisher=Japan Football Association |access-date=1 January 2024}}</ref>

